Guild participation shall be counted at the BEGINNING of raid, and rolls will be made for each worthy item using a proportional roll (i.e. GS has 6 participants, KoF has 13 participants = /random 1-19 with 1-6 = GS, 7-19 = KoF). Each guild may then decide how to distribute said loot using their own policy. ANY raid attendees who are not in zone, ready to raid at the posted raid time will NOT be counted towards their guild's total number for loot.<br>
<br>
Other raid participants (those not in the GS/KoF alliance) that are invited to a raid are the responsibility of the guild leading the raid, and may have loot distributed to them at their discretion following a winning roll for that guild.<br>
<br>
At times specific arrangments for certain items may be made at the raid leaders discrection, announced at the begining of said raid.<br>
<br>
It is the intent of this loot distribution policy that if no one in the winning guild CaWU the item and someone else CaWU, that the winning guild would then forgo that item for the good of the alliance.<br>
<br>
Also, in an attempt to best distribute loot and equip our members, the alliance has agreed to the following with regards to Velious BP distribution:<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">Vindi BP will be restricted to melee shaman.<br>
Statue BP will be restricted to melee.<br>
HoT BP will be restricted to clerics.</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
All alliance members will only be allowed <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">ONE</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> of these BPs. Once you win one you may not roll on a different one (i.e. if you are wearing a Vindi BP, you may not roll on one from Statue).<br>
<br>
The intention is to obtain this quality of BP for everyone in the alliance. This agreement establishes our priorities at this time. These restrictions will be lifted once a significant force of the alliance is outfitted with these BPs. Those wearing Thurgadin quest BPs are asked to carefully consider their upgrade path and timing.<br>
